53580A54EF9C4D0D96F5D04FFD46FD48.description:
write using a variety of grade-appropriate sentence lengths, patterns, and
connecting words to combine phrases, clauses, and sentences in increasingly
accurate ways as more English is acquired;

C1599537BAA449BCB29EFC024A4878E6.description:
edit writing for standard grammar and usage, including subject-verb
agreement, pronoun agreement, and appropriate verb tenses commensurate with
grade-level expectations as more English is acquired;

31A41281D641473B884E5548FBEFFFB1.description:
demonstrate comprehension of increasingly complex English by participating
in shared reading, retelling or summarizing material, responding to questions, and
taking notes commensurate with content area and grade level needs;

DD630ADB8F204942A64E07694BC090CA.description:
use pre-reading supports such as graphic organizers, illustrations, and
pre-taught topic-related vocabulary and other pre-reading activities to enhance
comprehension of written text;

3FD7DEE1DF954CBF9F7DDE8222E47C34.description:
develop basic sight vocabulary, derive meaning of environmental print, and
comprehend English vocabulary and language structures used routinely in written
classroom materials;

80CDED1288EC4412B0780C17D264929F.description:
 learn relationships between sounds and letters of the English language and
decode (sound out) words using a combination of skills such as recognizing
sound-letter relationships and identifying cognates, affixes, roots, and base words;

B2F43AEFBF4140D98BF6288033185C6C.description:
express opinions, ideas, and feelings ranging from communicating single
words and short phrases to participating in extended discussions on a variety of
social and grade-appropriate academic topics;

5ED6675239D7428FB9BBB21482ED2F90.description:
speak using a variety of grammatical structures, sentence lengths, sentence
types, and connecting words with increasing accuracy and ease as more English is
acquired;

17EDFD52446D485C88A3C445A876AAA7.description:
practice producing sounds of newly acquired vocabulary such as long and
short vowels, silent letters, and consonant clusters to pronounce English words in
a manner that is increasingly comprehensible;

45BDF1C0E7984587819A66A2B04775C3.description:
understand the general meaning, main points, and important details of spoken
language ranging from situations in which topics, language, and contexts are
familiar to unfamiliar;

167EB9EB55964F5FB09A93423ADEFCD9.description:
listen to and derive meaning from a variety of media such as audio tape,
video, DVD, and CD ROM to build and reinforce concept and language
attainment;

CDA871EC206F42E8BAD72231059B6A30.description:
demonstrate an increasing ability to distinguish between formal and informal
English and an increasing knowledge of when to use each one commensurate with
grade-level learning expectations;

8525A6D41A194D6D8201D8635704EA6F.description:
internalize new basic and academic language by using and reusing it in
meaningful ways in speaking and writing activities that build concept and
language attainment;

AF9973D2E19C4623AA4944CA4BCD687C.description:
speak using learning strategies such as requesting assistance, employing nonverbal
cues, and using synonyms and circumlocution (conveying ideas by
defining or describing when exact English words are not known);

F1356E7EEBB6441EAF530233D62FEA2F.description:
use strategic learning techniques such as concept mapping, drawing,
memorizing, comparing, contrasting, and reviewing to acquire basic and grade level
vocabulary;
